data.text:
New York: G.P. Putnam's Sons, 1970. Very Good / Very Good. Item #29824

New York: G.P. Putnam's Sons, 1970. First Edition. Octavo. 401 pp. Illustrated dust jacket with $6.95 price present. Dark blue cloth stamped in gilt. Dust jacket worn and creased along edges and folds; neat tape repair at top of spine; mild scuffing; faint stain to rear panel verso. Boards show light shelfwear and a touch faded; slight gilt flecks to front and spine. Bit of separation at crown but binding sound. Abrasion to front free endpaper; interior else unmarked. Overall a Very Good copy of a title often found in lesser condition.
